    • Field Detail

      • pickupsDisabled

        public ArrayList<String> pickupsDisabled
        List of pickups types that are disabled. For example, when eating a slowdown pickup, we don't want the player to be able to eat another slowdown pickup while the effect is active, and we also don't want the player to eat a speedup pickup, since that would mean 2 pickups affecting speed are in effect at the same time.

      • setDirection

        public void setDirection​(char dirNew)
        Sets direction of the Snake If dirNew is the opposite of current direction, the direction is not changed. That would allow the Snake to turn around into itself, which means Game Over.
        Parameters:
        dirNew - new direction

      • getBoard

        public int[][] getBoard()
        Returns 2 dimensional int array of map. Values consist of: Empty cells = 0 Pickups = 1 Snake = 2
        Returns:
        int[][] array of map

      • move

        public void move()
        Moves Snake by 1 tile direction is determined by direction variable. If after move, Snake head collides with any other body part, Snake dies. After every move, it is checked if head is at position of any pickup. If true, then pickup is eaten, and points are added to player.

      • placeRandomPickup

        public void placeRandomPickup()
        Places random pickup to random empty cell.

      • getPickupIndexCollidingWithHead

        public int getPickupIndexCollidingWithHead()
        Returns:
        index of pickup that is at the same position as Snake's head, returns -1 if no collision
